history.content:
Taking 70 before 16A will definitely leave you spending a lot more time on the class than average, as you'll be missing the linear algebra foundations that the course assumes. Regardless of which class you take in the summer, I strongly encourage you to take 16A before diving into 70.

That said, I think 16A is being offered over summer for the first time, so it might be fun to be part of the pilot. However, if you're looking for an experience that's long established, you could take 61BL instead. I suppose if you really want the Hug experience, go for 16A over summer. Both classes are relatively similar in terms of coursework in my opinion, depending of course on your mathematical and CS background. If you feel like you're particularly better suited to learn math faster, take 16A. If you'll likely learn CS faster, take 61BL.

I'm looking to take either EE16a or cs61bl over summer but am not sure which one to do. If I do ee16a during summer, I would take 61b with hug fall and 70 in spring to try and declare. If I take 61bl, I could take 70 in fall and try to declare, but am not confident in my math maturity to do 70 since ive only taken math 1a and 1b (and am missing out on hug since people say he is good). Does anyone have any feedback on taking ee16a over summer, cause I can't seem to find any. Thank you!
history.subject: EE16a or cs61b summer
